collections.name: Climbing
collections.description: You dine, the restaurant climbs. Climbing on Resy is the only data-driven list powered by your reservations. Consider it a curated guide by locals, for locals.

content.body: Once you’ve realized that the mastermind behind 4 Charles is also behind this swanky spot, it’ll come as no surprise that Au Cheval boasts one of the country’s most lauded and beloved burgers.
content.name: why_we_like_it

about.body: Hidden down Cortlandt Alley, Au Cheval reimagines traditional fare, from roasted bone marrow to salads, griddled cheeseburgers to seafood selections and of course, prime steaks. Guests can enjoy strong, classic cocktails, a global wine list and a robust selection of draught beers while lounging in leather booths, or seated at the zinc bar, while the open kitchen works to a pulsating and resonant soundtrack.

need_to_know.body:
Au Cheval is accepting reservations up to 14 days in advance with each new day becoming available at 9 AM EST.
We are an intimate restaurant and accept reservations for parties of 1-6 guests. We kindly ask that you do not make multiple reservations for more than one group. Counter seating is available for walk-in guests on a first come first serve basis.

A $2.50 per person reservation fee will be added to all reservations made online. Holiday fees may vary. This is to secure your seats with us. We do not charge a reservation fee for walk-in guests.
